# CAD Analysis Engine — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

[cad_analysis_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/Shreyas Durge/Downloads/bar-subjected-to-axial-loads-1.snapshot.1/cad_analysis_engine.py) — a single ~370-line Python script implementing the full pipeline:

| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| **STL loader** | `trimesh` — extracts all 18+ metrics including degenerate faces, non-manifold edges, watertight, euler number, etc. |
| **STEP/IGES loader** | `pythonocc-core` (OCP or OCC.Core) — face/edge/vertex/solid/shell counts, exact volume, surface area, tessellated triangles, STEP units |
| **Edge selection** | Direction-based filtering (±Z, ±X) using BRepAdaptor_Curve tangent at midpoint |
| **Modifications** | Fillet (r=1.0) on Z-aligned edges, Chamfer (d=0.5) on X-aligned edges |
| **Validation** | 6 flag types: `read_failure`, `degenerate_geometry`, `non_manifold_geometry`, `not_watertight`, `missing_metrics`, `invalid_topology` |
| **Confidence scoring** | Starts at 1.0, penalty per flag, clamped [0, 1] |
| **Graceful degradation** | STEP/IGES paths return `read_failure` when pythonocc-core is unavailable |

